# Docker & Infrastructure

## Docker Compose

- `docker-compose.yml` at repo root defines local development services.
- PostgreSQL 16 Alpine as the shared database server (each service uses a separate database).
- Init scripts in `docker/postgres-init/` for creating additional databases on first run.

## Service Ports (local dev)

| Service | Container | Host Port |
|---------|-----------|-----------|
| PostgreSQL | hospitalmeals-postgres | 5433 |
| Auth API | hospitalmeals-auth-api | 8080 |
| Patient API | hospitalmeals-patient-api | 8081 |
| Meals API | (to be added) | 8082 |
| Kitchen API | (to be added) | 8083 |
| Frontend | (to be added) | 4200 |

## Dockerfile Pattern

All backend services use multi-stage builds:

```dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0 AS base    # Runtime
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0 AS build       # Build + restore
FROM build AS publish                                  # Publish
FROM base AS final                                     # Copy published output
```

- Build context is the domain parent folder (e.g., `Backend/Meals/`).
- Expose port 8080 via `ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:8080`.

## Database

- Each service has its own PostgreSQL database:
  - `hospitalmeals_auth_db`
  - `hospitalmeals_patient_db`
  - `hospitalmeals_meals_db`
  - `hospitalmeals_kitchen_db`
- EF migrations run automatically on startup via `HostedService`.
- Connection strings passed via environment variables in docker-compose.

## Configuration

- Sensitive config (JWT keys, connection strings) via environment variables — never commit to `appsettings.json`.
- `appsettings.json` only contains non-sensitive defaults (logging, allowed hosts).
- `appsettings.Development.json` for local dev overrides (gitignored).
